      <akn:section eId="sec_47_867">
        <akn:num>47-867</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Public charter school real property tax rebate.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_47-867_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A public charter school that leases a school facility from an entity subject to tax under this chapter shall receive a rebate of that portion of the tax, if any, that represents the public charter school’s pro rata share of the lessor’s tax on the property if:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_47-867_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The rebate shall be the amount of the portion of the tax paid by the public charter school.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_47-867_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The application shall include:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_47-867_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>If a proper application has been made, the Mayor shall rebate the tax on or before December 31 of the same calendar year.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
    </akn:body>
